data.enText: a state of complete confusion and lack of order

data.chText: 经济 / 政治 / 国内的混乱
大雪导致道路上交通一片混乱。
data.enText: Heavy snow has caused total chaos on the roads.

data.chText: 聚会后，房子里一片狼藉。
data.enText: The house was in chaos after the party.

ex.enText: The books on the desk are in disorder.

ex.chText: 整个计划被搞得乱七八糟。
ex.enText: The whole plan was thrown into disorder.

synonyms.bx: 指杂乱无章、混乱无序的状态。

ex.enText: There was complete chaos in the square.

ex.chText: 他的辞职引发了该国的政治动乱。
ex.enText: His resignation triggered political chaos in the country.

synonyms.bx: 指一切事物均无组织无秩序的大混乱状态。

ex.chText: 他看到的是难以形容的混乱场面。
ex.enText: What he saw was a scene of indescribable confusion.

ex.chText: 敌人开始进攻，村子里哭声和喊声交织在一起，乱作一团。
ex.enText: There was a confusion of cries and yells in the village as the enemy started to attack.

synonyms.bx: 通常指嘈杂纷乱、令人难以理解或控制的局面。

ex.chText: 敌人的突袭使整个城市陷入一片混乱。
ex.enText: The enemy's raid threw the whole city into disarray.

ex.chText: 这一决定使公司完全陷入混乱。
ex.enText: This decision left the company in total disarray.

ex.chText: 聚会之后房子里一片狼藉。
ex.enText: The house is a complete mess after the party.
The kitchen was left in an awful mess.

ex.chText: 别呆在我的卧室里，不然你会把那里搞得乱七八糟。
ex.enText: Get out of my bedroom, or you'll make a mess in it.

synonyms.bx: 指某个地方又脏又乱的状态。

tr: (physics) a dynamical system that is extremely sensitive to its initial conditions
the formless and disordered state of matter before the creation of the cosmos
a state of extreme confusion and disorder

value.def: Chaos is a state of complete disorder and confusion.

example.ex: The world's first transatlantic balloon race ended in chaos last night...
example.tran: 昨晚世界第一届跨大西洋热气球比赛在一片混乱中收场。

example.ex: It is impossible to establish democracy amid economic chaos.
example.tran: 经济秩序混乱不堪，是不可能建立民主的。

types.define: CHAOS是SCI一区的顶尖数学杂志，刊登非线性动力学和非线性物理具有重要原创性的高水平研究论文。
